Pauli operations: Pauli matricies

II (identity matrix), \sigma_x = X (bit flip); Y = \sigma_y, Z
=\sigma_z (phase flip)

H = Hadamard = (1/sqrt(2) 1/sqrt(2)
    	        1/sqrt(2) -1/sqrt(2))

H goes from standard basis to |+> + |->

P = Phase operation
(1 0)
(0 e^{i\theta})

II = P_0
Z = P_\pi

H converts from |0> to |+> and H|1> to |-> and back again

Independent operations M on X and N on Y is equivalent to M [tensor
product] N performed on system (X, Y)


--! Bell states are entangled states that represent a basis for ALL
    multi-bit states, entangled or not!

